msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 6"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:0.5"
msgid "6. Dutiyasahaseyyasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The second training rule on the same sleeping place"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.18, pts-cs-bu-pc6.1, pts-vp-en.2.198, ms2V_182
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: janapade → janapadesu (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā anuruddho kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ "
"gacchanto sāyaṃ aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upagacchi."
msgstr ""
"At that time, while Venerable Anuruddha was walking through the Kosalan "
"country on his way to Sāvatthī, one evening he arrived at a certain village."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena tasmiṃ gāme aññatarissā itthiyā āvasathāgāraṃ "
"paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Just then a woman in that village had prepared her guest house."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ "
"itthiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Anuruddha approached that woman and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.5"
msgid "“sace te, bhagini, agaru, vaseyyāma ekarattaṃ āvasathāgāre”ti."
msgstr ""
"“If it’s not inconvenient for you, I’d like to stay in your guest house for "
"one night.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.6"
msgid "“Vaseyyātha, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“Please stay, Venerable.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.7"
msgid ""
"Aññepi addhikā yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ "
"etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Other travelers also approached that woman and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.8"
msgid "“sace te, ayye, agaru vaseyyāma ekarattaṃ āvasathāgāre”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Madam, if it’s not troublesome for you, we’d like to stay in your guest "
"house for one night.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.9"
msgid "“Eso kho ayyo samaṇo paṭhamaṃ upagato;"
msgstr "“Sirs, an ascetic is already staying there."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.10"
msgid "sace so anujānāti, vaseyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "If he agrees, you may stay.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te addhikā yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Those travelers then approached Anuruddha and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.12"
msgid "“sace te, bhante, agaru, vaseyyāma ekarattaṃ āvasathāgāre”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, if it’s not troublesome for you, we’d like to stay one night in "
"the guest house.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.13"
msgid "“Vaseyyātha, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Please stay.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.19, ms2V_183
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī āyasmante anuruddhe saha dassanena paṭibaddhacittā ahosi."
msgstr ""
"Now as soon as that woman had seen Anuruddha, she had fallen in love with "
"him."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.199
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "She now approached him and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.16"
msgid "“ayyo, bhante, imehi manussehi ākiṇṇo na phāsu viharissati."
msgstr "“Venerable, you won’t be at ease surrounded by these people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.17"
msgid "Sādhāhaṃ, bhante, ayyassa mañcakaṃ abbhantaraṃ paññapeyyan”ti."
msgstr "It would be good if I prepared a bed for you in the main house.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.18"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā anuruddho tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "Anuruddha consented by remaining silent."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.19"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī āyasmato anuruddhassa mañcakaṃ abbhantaraṃ paññapetvā "
"alaṅkatappaṭiyattā gandhagandhinī yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""
"After preparing a bed in the main house, she put on jewelery and perfume, "
"and she approached Anuruddha and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.20"
msgid ""
"“ayyo, bhante, abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko, ahañcamhi abhirūpā dassanīyā "
"pāsādikā."
msgstr "“Venerable, you’re good-looking and graceful, and so am I."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.21"
msgid "Sādhāhaṃ, bhante, ayyassa pajāpati bhaveyyan”ti."
msgstr "It would be good, Venerable, if I were to become your wife.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.22"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā anuruddho tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "But Anuruddha remained silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.23"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "She said the same thing a second time, but again got no response."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.24"
msgid "tatiyampi kho sā itthī āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And a third time she said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.25"
msgid ""
"“ayyo, bhante, abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko, ahañcamhi abhirūpā dassanīyā "
"pāsādikā."
msgstr "“Venerable, you’re good-looking and graceful, and so am I."

#. VAR: paṭicchatu → sampaṭicchatu (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.26"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, ayyo mañceva paṭicchatu sabbañca sāpateyyan”ti."
msgstr "It would be good, Venerable, if you took me and all this property.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.27"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā anuruddho tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "But Anuruddha remained silent for a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.28"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī sāṭakaṃ nikkhipitvā āyasmato anuruddhassa purato "
"caṅkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi seyyampi kappeti."
msgstr ""
"She then threw off her clothes, and she walked up and down, stood, sat down, "
"and lay down in front of him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.29"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho indriyāni okkhipitvā taṃ itthiṃ neva olokesi napi "
"ālapi."
msgstr ""
"But Anuruddha controlled his senses and neither looked at nor spoke to her."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.30"
msgid "Atha kho sā itthī—"
msgstr "Then that woman said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.31"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "“It’s astonishing and amazing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.32"
msgid "Bahū me manussā satenapi sahassenapi pahiṇanti."
msgstr "Many people send for me with a hundred or a thousand coins."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.33"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ pana samaṇo—mayā sāmaṃ yāciyamāno—na icchati mañceva paṭicchituṃ "
"sabbañca sāpateyyan”ti "
msgstr ""
"But this ascetic, even when begged by me, does not want me and all this "
"property.”"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.200
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.34"
msgid ""
"sāṭakaṃ nivāsetvā āyasmato anuruddhassa pādesu sirasā nipatitvā āyasmantaṃ "
"anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""
"After dressing, she bowed down with her head at Anuruddha’s feet and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.35"
msgid ""
"“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ yāhaṃ "
"evamakāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, I’ve committed an offense, in that foolishly, confused, and "
"unskillfully I acted like this."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.36"
msgid ""
"Tassā me, bhante, ayyo accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Venerable, please forgive me for my offense so that I may restrain myself in "
"the future.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.37"
msgid ""
"“Taggha tvaṃ, bhagini, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ "
"yā tvaṃ evamakāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Certainly you have committed an offense, in that foolishly, confused, and "
"unskillfully you acted like this."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.38"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho tvaṃ, bhagini, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, "
"taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr ""
"But since you acknowledge your offense and you make amends for it in "
"accordance with the Teaching, I forgive you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.39"
msgid ""
"Vuddhi hesā, bhagini, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ "
"paṭikaroti āyatiñca saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For this is called growth in the training of the noble ones, that is, "
"acknowledging an offense, making amends in accordance with the Teaching, and "
"undertaking restraint for the future.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_184
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.40"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī tassā rattiyā accayena āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ paṇītena "
"khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā sampavāretvā, āyasmantaṃ "
"anuruddhaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"The following morning that woman personally served and satisfied Anuruddha "
"with various kinds of fine food. When he had finished his meal and had "
"washed his hands and bowl, she bowed and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.41"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ itthiṃ āyasmā anuruddho dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr "And Anuruddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.42"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī—āyasmatā anuruddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā "
"samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā—āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "She then said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.43"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“Wonderful, Venerable, wonderful!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.44"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr ""
"Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what had "
"been hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the "
"darkness so that one with eyes might see what is there—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.45"
msgid "evamevaṃ ayyena anuruddhena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "even so has Anuruddha made the Teaching clear in many ways."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.46"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr ""
"Venerable, I go for refuge to the Master and to the Teaching and to the "
"Order of monks."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.201
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.47"
msgid "Upāsikaṃ maṃ ayyo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please accept me as a lay follower who from today has gone for refuge for "
"life.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_185
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.48"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards, after arriving at Sāvatthī, Anuruddha told the monks about "
"what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.49"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.50"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Anuruddha,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.51"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā anuruddho mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappessatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Anuruddha sleep in the same sleeping place as a woman?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_186
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.52"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.53"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, anuruddha, mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Anuruddha, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.54"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.55"
msgid ""
"Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe … kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, anuruddha, mātugāmena "
"sahaseyyaṃ kappessasi."
msgstr "Anuruddha, how can you sleep in the same sleeping place as a woman?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.56"
msgid "Netaṃ, anuruddha, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.57"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.57a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_187
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:1.58"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappeyya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk sleeps in the same sleeping place as a woman, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc6.2.1, ms2V_188
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_189
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.5"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: yakkhī → yakkhinī (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.6"
msgid "manussitthī, na yakkhī, na petī, na tiracchānagatā;"
msgstr ""
"a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.7"
msgid "antamaso tadahujātāpi dārikā, pageva mahattarī."
msgstr "even a girl born on that very day, all the more an older one."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_190
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.8"
msgid "Sahāti"
msgstr "Same:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_191
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.10"
msgid "Seyyā nāma"
msgstr "Sleeping place:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"sabbacchannā, sabbaparicchannā, yebhuyyenacchannā, yebhuyyena paricchannā."
msgstr "fully roofed, fully walled; mostly roofed, mostly walled."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-pli4.20, ms2V_192
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.12"
msgid "Seyyaṃ kappeyyāti"
msgstr "Sleeps […] in the same sleeping place"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.13"
msgid ""
"atthaṅgate sūriye, mātugāme nipanne bhikkhu nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"when the sun has set: if the monk lies down when the woman is already lying "
"down, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.202
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhu nipanne mātugāmo nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if the woman lies down when the monk is already lying down, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.15"
msgid "Ubho vā nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.1.16"
msgid "Uṭṭhahitvā punappunaṃ nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc12, pts-cs-bu-pc6.2.2, ms2V_193
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.1"
msgid "Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he sleeps in the same "
"sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.2"
msgid "Mātugāme vematiko sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a woman, but he is unsure if she is, and he sleeps in the same "
"sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.3"
msgid "Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he sleeps in "
"the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_194
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.4"
msgid "Upaḍḍhacchanne upaḍḍhaparicchanne, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is half-roofed and half-walled, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatitthiyā vā sahaseyyaṃ "
"kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he sleeps in the same sleeping place as a female spirit, a female ghost, "
"a sexual nonconformist, or a female animal, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.6"
msgid "Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.7"
msgid "Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.2.8"
msgid "Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no "
"offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-cs-bu-pc6.2.3, ms2V_195
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

#. VAR: sabbaaparicchanne, sabbaparicchanne sabbaacchanne → anāpatti sabbaacchanne sabba­apa­ricchanne (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.2"
msgid "sabbacchanne sabbaaparicchanne,"
msgstr "if it is fully roofed, but not walled;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.3"
msgid "sabbaparicchanne sabbaacchanne,"
msgstr "if it is fully walled, but not roofed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.4"
msgid "yebhuyyena acchanne,"
msgstr "if it is mostly not roofed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.5"
msgid "yebhuyyena aparicchanne,"
msgstr "if it is mostly not walled;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.6"
msgid "mātugāme nipanne bhikkhu nisīdati,"
msgstr "if the monk sits when the woman is lying down;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.7"
msgid "bhikkhu nipanne mātugāmo nisīdati,"
msgstr "if the woman sits when the monk is lying down;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.8"
msgid "ubho vā nisīdanti,"
msgstr "if they both sit down together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.9"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.10"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_196
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc6:2.3.11"
msgid "Dutiyasahaseyyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The sixth rule, the second training rule on the same sleeping place, is "
"finished."
